721005f-a.text:
The Lexington Ave. Building (17-stories), Nos. 464-466 Lexington Ave., west side, from West 45th (right) to 46th Streets. This view shows the rear of the building, with its entrance for trucks facing on a 50 foot alley,which separates it from the New York Central Building through which passes Park AVe. traffic. Also shown is a general view eastward, with the East River and Oueensborough Bridge appearing in
the background.
October 11, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
